newsitem.title: JORDAN: Jordan overnight rates in 3.75-4.25 pct range.
newsitem.headline: Jordan overnight rates in 3.75-4.25 pct range.

text.p: Overnight rates on the Jordanian dinar hovered in a narrow 3.75-4.25 percent range on Tuesday, up from 3.00 to 4.00 percent on Monday with excess liquidity still dampening overall demand, traders said.
"The market is still very liquid but banks are waiting for next Saturday after the new CD issue, which is expected to drain excess funds," said one dealer.
Dealers say maturing CDs (certificates of deposit), a number of CD repos by banks and injection of dinar funds into the banking system had recently depressed rates.
